            <!-- Additional Content -->
            <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
                <h2>What Makes Great Gaming Headphones?</h2>
                <p>When choosing gaming headphones, consider these key factors:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Sound Quality:</strong> Clear audio for immersive gaming experience</li>
                    <li><strong>Microphone:</strong> Clear voice communication with teammates</li>
                    <li><strong>Comfort:</strong> Comfortable for extended gaming sessions</li>
                    <li><strong>Compatibility:</strong> Works with your gaming platform (PC, PS5, Xbox)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <!-- Features Section -->
            <div class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-8 text-center">
                    What to Look For in Gaming Headphones
                </h2>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Sound Quality</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Look for headphones with clear, balanced audio that can reproduce game sounds accurately. Surround sound capabilities can enhance immersion.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Microphone Quality</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            A clear microphone is essential for team communication. Look for noise-cancelling microphones that filter out background noise.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Comfort</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Gaming sessions can last for hours, so comfort is crucial. Look for lightweight designs with soft ear cushions and adjustable headbands.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Compatibility</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Ensure the headphones work with your gaming platform. Some headphones are optimized for specific consoles or PC gaming.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <div class="mb-12">
                <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-2xl sm:text-3xl mb-8 text-center">
                    Frequently Asked Questions
                </h2>
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Do I need a gaming headset or can I use regular headphones?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            While you can use regular headphones, gaming headsets are specifically designed for gaming with features like clear microphones, optimized sound profiles, and gaming-specific features.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Are wireless gaming headphones worth it?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            Wireless gaming headphones offer freedom of movement and eliminate cable clutter. However, wired options often provide lower latency and don't require charging.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-hover">
                        <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">What's the difference between 7.1 and stereo sound?</h3>
                        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
                            7.1 surround sound provides directional audio cues for better spatial awareness in games, while stereo offers standard left-right audio. Both can work well depending on your preferences.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
